Q2.
(Code): TMDB paginates results with a page parameter. Write a function that retrieves all pages of a search query (not just page 1), using the total_pages value from the first response to know when to stop.






TipAnswer Q2





search_all_pages &lt;- function(query, key) {
  first_resp &lt;- resp_body_json(req_perform(
    request("https://api.themoviedb.org/3/search/movie") |&gt;
      req_url_query(api_key = key, query = query, page = 1)
  ))

  total_pages &lt;- min(first_resp$total_pages, 5)  # cap at 5 to be polite

  all_pages &lt;- lapply(seq_len(total_pages), function(p) {
    data &lt;- resp_body_json(req_perform(
      request("https://api.themoviedb.org/3/search/movie") |&gt;
        req_url_query(api_key = key, query = query, page = p)
    ))
    lapply(data$results, function(m) data.frame(title = m$title, vote_average = m$vote_average)) |&gt;
      bind_rows()
  }) |&gt; bind_rows()

  all_pages
}
Capping at 5 pages avoids hammering the API — always be a polite client.




